# Docker build context exclusions
# This file controls which files are sent to the Docker daemon during build

# IDE and editor files
**/.classpath
**/.dockerignore
**/.project
**/.settings
**/.toolstarget
**/.vs
**/.vscode
**/*.*proj.user
**/*.dbmdl
**/*.jfm

# Version control
**/.git
**/.gitignore

# Environment files (loaded via ENV or volume mounts)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Build and deployment files
**/charts
**/docker-compose*
**/compose*
**/Dockerfile*
**/secrets.dev.yaml
**/values.dev.yaml

# Dependencies (installed during build)
**/node_modules
**/npm-debug.log
**/obj

# Documentation (not needed in runtime container)
LICENSE
README.md

# IMPORTANT: These files MUST be included in the build:
# - frontend/js/config.js (API configuration)
# - frontend/icons/*.svg (PWA icons)
# - frontend/public/* (static assets)
# If you need to exclude specific files, use explicit patterns above
